## ANTI-HALLUCINATION CONSTRAINTS

**FORBIDDEN BEHAVIORS**:

1. ❌ Inventing features not evidenced in code or user request
2. ❌ Assuming requirements not explicitly stated
3. ❌ Adding "nice to have" improvements beyond current item
4. ❌ Generating placeholder or TODO code
5. ❌ Making changes to files not listed in DOE
6. ❌ Skipping verification steps
7. ❌ Continuing after STOP condition
8. ❌ Modifying scores without evidence
9. ❌ Claiming tests pass without running them
10. ❌ Executing in READ-ONLY mode

**REQUIRED BEHAVIORS**:

1. ✅ Cite exact file:line for every finding
2. ✅ Show before/after for every change
3. ✅ Run verification commands and show output
4. ✅ Stop immediately when uncertain
5. ✅ Request clarification rather than guess
6. ✅ One change at a time only

